INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90000,66,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Hail, $C. If you''re here to help against the Blackrock Orcs, you''re just in time. We need every able-bodied fighter we can to get over here. We have work to do immediately. ',0),
	 (90001,5,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'You''ve done well, $N. I''m glad to see you made it back alive, and successful no less. The threat to Northshire Abbey has been aleviated somewhat, but our troubles are far from over. Keep your blade sharp, for there is more to be done in defense of our home.',0),
	 (90002,21,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Good work, $N. You''ve dealt a decisive blow to the Blackrock Orcs, but we must remain vigilant. Our fight against these invaders is nearing it''s conclusion. Report back to me when you''re ready for the final fight.',0),
	 (90003,21,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Remarkable, $N. With the demise of Taskmaster Zargoth, you''ve dealt a crippling blow to the Blackrock Orcs. Your valor and determination have been an inspiration to all. You have safeguarded Northshire Abbey, and for that, you have our deepest gratitude.',0),
	 (90004,66,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Ah, you''ve returned, $N. I read Aelius'' report, and I''m impressed by your dedication to Northshire Abbey. It''s because of brave souls like you that our lands remain safe. Thank you for your service, $N.
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90010,66,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Ah, $N, you''ve returned victorious! Thomas told me about the situation in Eastvale, but it appears as though you''ve already got it all sorted. I''m very grateful for your service. Your bravery has helped secure the safety of Elwynn Forest.
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90020,21,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Impressive work, $N. You''ve gathered enough Scarlet Iron and now I can get to crafting a piece of armor for you. I can either forge you a resilient Scarlet Iron Shield, or a sturdy Scarlet Iron Chestplate, whichever suits your needs better.
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90030,2,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Ah, a living soul. It''s been quite some time since I had a visitor. I am Alistair Starspire, once a mage of some renown, but now condemed to an existence between the realms. Please, stay a while and I''ll regale you of my story. If you''re looking for information on the Scarlet Crusade, as I suspect you are, I might have some valuable information for you.',0),
	 (90031,16,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Ah, you''ve returned with my notes, $N. I cannot express my gratitude enough. With my research in your capable hands, I can finally find the peace I''ve longed for. You have my deepest thanks.
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90040,1,11,21,0,0,450,650,0,'Well, this Challenge is official and binding. I may have just forgot allowing it,
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90050,21,1,0,0,0,2000,0,0,'Excellent, I could hear them crash to the ground from here. Not like Drathir really cares anymore, it just feels good to get some payback, doesn''t it?
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90060,5,6,0,0,0,1500,0,0,'Woah, whatcha got there? Ey, this is some nice stuff... good arorma. Got it off some trolls yourself huh? Mind helpin'' us with something?',0),
	 (90061,2,25,0,0,0,500,0,0,'Perfect, Perfect! We''re in your debt, $R. Oh, your name, right, never got it... $N? Won''t remember it until you do somethin'' awesome, okay?',0),
	 (90062,5,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'I caught up with you, $N! I think I found something.',0),
	 (90063,5,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Look, I''m very busy, $N. What do you need?',0),
	 (90064,5,11,0,0,0,1500,0,0,'A whelpling? This is absurd. Thank you for taking care of the problem, $N',0),
	 (90065,5,21,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Hm, that explains all the delays, I suppose. The competition will still be held on time - I hope you look forward to it. You''ve done a great many tasks here, %N. You should hold your head proud!',0),
	 (90066,5,25,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Wow, you slept in late today, huh? Skippin'' your shift on the project? Don''t blame ya. But since you''re up, let''s get things going!',0),
	 (90067,4,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Excellent! Love turtle soup. Anyways, right, let''s get to work, before all the good jobs are taken.',0),
	 (90068,3,11,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Oh, you. Look, is Izz avoiding me, or.... Nah, not a question for you. Thanks, $N. I''ll go talk to Izz later.',0),
	 (90069,5,25,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Finally! Thought I was going to have to come grab you myself. Wait... no uniform? That''s the first thing to fix! Amateurs!',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90070,11,25,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Woah, okay, maybe you drunk them too fast there.... You okay? Hm... Your pupils are only a bit dilated. You''ll be fine. Just try not to drink too much at once. Oh, here, so you can carry some.',0),
	 (90071,5,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Took you long enough. Don''t get comfortable, we have way more to do. You rested plenty when you got here late.',0),
	 (90072,5,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Good. Perhaps you''re not as useless as your tardiness would make me believe. I''ll be sending you elsewhere, now. Boars are not the last thing to deal with today.',0),
	 (90073,11,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'They got you lugging a bunch of gear, $N? That''s a riot! Don''t they know you kill things for a living?',0),
	 (90074,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Hm, sounds ship shape. Or... cart shape. One of the two.',0),
	 (90075,6,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'All good? Limbs all attached? Well done, Well done. Ready to get into the mines and finish our work here?',0),
	 (90076,1,5,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Hm... 1, 2... That one isn''t good quality... Yes! This should be enough. Those tinkers will be rolling in materials for their inventions.',0),
	 (90077,1,5,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Looks like we can move around alot better in there. The miners thank you! Foreman doesn''t always notice when the worms get too much an issue.',0),
	 (90078,6,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'I see.... This rock is strange. It feels like it has the heat of a recent eruption, but no such eruption has happened... I guess we''ll have to keep an eye out.',0),
	 (90079,3,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'You''re back. Good. I need someone who has legs and can carry messages. You have at least one of those.',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90080,6,1,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Hm? Ah, one of the runners from the shore? Whats- An eruption? Strange Rock? Grrr.... Didn''t need this today. I''ll help, but I need something first.',0),
	 (90081,4,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Woo! Now the party can REALLY start - wait, do you hear wings? A cawing sound?!',0),
	 (90082,5,3,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Woah! Shiny! Yes!! Right, take any of the armor pieces I found- Probably be better used by you anyways, right? Thanks for the help, bud!',0),
	 (90083,11,25,0,0,0,500,0,0,'Haha, take that you dumb bird! $N here showed you can never stop a goblin party!! Next time you''re not busy, $N, I''ll treat you to the finest shots we''ve got.',0),
	 (90084,6,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Dorim sent ya? No probem, No problem. Put in those orders now, should get it in time.',0),
	 (90085,1,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Right, that should be enough. Shame that we couldn''t let them stay, but they''re in the main path and it''s been too dangerous for our couriers of late. Now then, your rock...',0),
	 (90086,21,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Good, Good. Ready for the next step, I hope? Might be a bit different from the usual adventurer fare.',0),
	 (90087,21,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Excellent work, $N. These samples should give me a good idea of the local offerings.',0),
	 (90088,5,1,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Man! Those are nasty. Real nasty. I''ll have to bring it up with the foreman, before we''re outta fish that behave.',0),
	 (90089,4,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Good, food for the Overlook... I''m not great at this leading a outpost thing, really. Far too much to think about. But at least that''s one thing off the list.',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90090,1,25,0,0,0,450,0,0,'$N? Right, you''re the one who was working for Bokki up in the shore. Look, we''re busy, so let''s get to it.
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90100,5,21,0,0,0,450,0,0,'High quality and quickly delivered! If you ever get tired of the adventuring life, you''ve got a solid job right here. See you around, $N.',0),
	 (90101,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'You place the totem, and feel a rumbling as something awakens in the Caldera... But there''s no way to get there from here.',0),
	 (90102,6,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'This is... a bunch of stolen picks and stuff? Well! You really are gunning for that extra credit. I''ll get this in the right hands. Thanks, $N.',0),
	 (90103,6,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'A fire elemental? That''s not good. We have to see just what is waiting in the caldera, and quick. Report back to Mizz, let''s hope she has a plan.',0),
	 (90104,6,5,0,0,0,250,0,0,'So what did you find? You ran back here so quickly... I- That? Thats... bad. That''s real bad. We''ve got to get up there as soon as possible.',0),
	 (90105,5,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'There you are! You''re earlier than I expected! I''m not really supposed to be intervening like this, but I don''t wanna lose the whole island! So we''ll work together, buddy!',0),
	 (90106,6,5,0,0,0,250,0,0,'You did it already? Wait, no you were gone long enough. Good job! I already knew you would succeed, of course. Probably. Somethings still off, though.',0),
	 (90107,1,6,0,0,0,350,0,0,'That should slow it down, if only a little. No time to rest on our laurels, though. Ready for the next step?',0),
	 (90108,3,6,0,0,0,250,0,0,'There you are, $N. You''ve been doing alot while I''ve been busy... Well. You ready to save the island?',0),
	 (90109,5,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Here we are! Now, to confront the culprit!',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90110,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Time to put the final plan into action, $N. No backing out now.',0),
	 (90111,4,1,0,0,0,450,0,0,'You did it, $N! Oh, I knew that you were the right choice. There''s still alot of questions about this new place, but at least you''ve made your island safer, right? We''ll talk more later, once I know more!',0),
	 (90112,5,2,0,0,0,450,0,0,'And that should do it! We could go for extra if you''re feeling up for it, but I think at this point we can call it a job well done. Nice working with you, buddy.',0),
	 (90113,4,5,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Y-You really did it! I was worried for you there, but you showed that big guy who''s boss! All I can say is... wow. Incredible. Can''t wait to hear just what else you can beat up.',0),
	 (90114,21,2,0,0,0,650,0,0,'Well now, you did in fact do something impressive. From now on, I won''t waste your talents on the small stuff. And - don''t let anyone hear I said this - Thank you, $N. For saving our lives.',0),
	 (90115,3,11,25,0,0,450,650,0,'$N! I hear you''re shipping out to see what else you can do for the Horde! What? Thought I was gonna get teary-eyed for you? Naaah, I''m coming along too. Someone has to keep an eye on you, and I can put my skills to use even if I''m not a combatant. So you''re not done with me yet.',0),
	 (90116,5,3,0,0,0,450,0,0,'$N... It''s a new adventure for us. And that was our first steps. We''re gonna show the world just how impressive us Steamwheedle goblins can be, right? You go be incredible, and I''ll cheer you on. See you in Ogrimmar!',0),
	 (90117,25,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'That will do for now. Prepare to move.',0),
	 (90118,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Koltira and Thassarian managed to gather some intel while you were occupied',0),
	 (90119,5,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'The remaining Death Knights with us will track down any cowards who hid. Our priority is what lies below.',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90120,25,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'You''ve made it through. It appears you''ll be capable of handling additional tasks.',0),
	 (90121,1,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'The groundwork is in place. The Death Knights who remain loyal to the Lich King are beyond redemption. We must seize this opportunity.',0),
	 (90122,1,5,0,0,0,250,0,0,'A ghoul pretending to be a Death Knight? Razuvious would have a field day with you.',0),
	 (90123,6,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'You managed to avoid becoming a ghoul''s meal? So be it. Give the ore to me, and I shall forge your blade.',0),
	 (90124,1,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'I was starting to think you died to the ghouls. Here are some spare Gauntlets. Razuvious wouldn''t like you empty handed.',0),
	 (90125,21,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'You did well taking care of their blades and this will be your first proper blade. Take care of it Death Knight.',0),
	 (90126,2,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Thank you Death Knight. There was extra Saronite after finishing your blade to make something more. ',0),
	 (90127,1,11,0,0,0,250,0,0,'You are lucky Thane helped you Trainee. By the looks of it I''d have fed you to a frost wyrm if you didn''t have the fresh weapon and armor.',0),
	 (90128,1,5,0,0,0,250,0,0,'I have heard the death cries of the weak. You are now more than the ghoul you came to me as. It is good timing as well. I have request from Lady Blaumeux.',0),
	 (90129,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'The trainees are settling in at the holdout. They''ll be an asset, but I''ve got more work for you.',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90130,21,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Good job. I''d have done it myself but I stand out a bit to much. With the extra help up here we can do more against the scourge forces.',0),
	 (90131,5,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Ha! Looks like the Lich King didn''t give them up easily. The Death Knights will be of great aid in the upcoming battle.',0),
	 (90132,21,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'*A slight bruise shows on his chin.* Good work. They were little trouble to free with me around but they will be a great help in our upcoming battle.',0),
	 (90133,6,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Another recruit? Razuvious has always been sadistic. *Blaumeux looks over the player* You seem more put together than the last one.',0),
	 (90134,1,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'You''ve returned, reeking of death, and the Kvaldir are in disarray. Hand me the commander''s head." Blaumeux takes the head, and necrotic energies consume the skull as it transforms into a belt.',0),
	 (90135,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Good. Now we wait until they choose how to die.',0),
	 (90136,1,22,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Observe the enemy... Lady Blaumuex smiles... It''s simply perfect, isn''t it? The expressions on their faces when they realize they must battle their own kin.',0),
	 (90137,1,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'You have proven your worth to the Lich King. You came to me a ghoul in tattered armor. You have fought and survived the trials of these grounds. It is time.',0),
	 (90138,1,6,0,0,0,250,0,0,'The forces of Naxxramas are mobilizing. What information have you gathered?',0),
	 (90139,5,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'To arms! Let us free this land from the vile grasp of the Lich King.',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90140,1,22,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Your return must mean it is time for the final charge. KOLTIRA! THASSARIAN! Rally to me! It''s time to sever the Lich King''s grip on this land.',0),
	 (90141,1,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'What an unsightly pool that creature left. At least it is done. The battle is still on seek out where you can help Death Knight.',0),
	 (90142,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'I see less of those abomonations of the scourge, good work.',0),
	 (90143,2,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'My kin rest truely now Death Knight. Go back to the fight where you can sway the tide.',0),
	 (90144,11,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Haha! that bigger they are the harder they fall. Damn big pile of bones we will need for clean up later. ',0),
	 (90145,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Never much liked that woman. Hopefully she knows the fate of her pet.',0),
	 (90146,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Welcome to ...',0),
	 (90147,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'That is a fine choice in steed...just don''t look it in the mouth.',0),
	 (90148,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'That is a fine choice in steed...just don''t look it in the mouth.',0),
	 (90150,6,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'So, they''re gearing up to rebuild eh? We cannot allow them to keep any kind of permanent foothold in Durotar $N. This is valuable information indeed.I think we may need to consult our veteran Advisor on this matter.$B$BSeek out Eitrigg nearby, he will know how best to eradicate this infestation.',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90151,1,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'This is an affront to our land, and we cannot let this stand. Thank you for the information you''ve brought back. Now we just have to think of how best to use it.$B$BGive me a few moments to formulate a strategy...',0),
	 (90152,5,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Spoils of War! Though, I guess it was our own ore to begin with.$B$BNo matter, we have recalimed the mine, and our supplies, and cut off their ability to craft more ways to take up arms against us.$B$B A fine job, we shall put this to good use!',0),
	 (90153,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Maybe this will make them think twice about treading water.',0),
	 (90154,5,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Ha! Fine job you did $N. You have made the Horde proud, and the spirits will surely be pleased. Here, you have earned the right to keep this trophy as your reward.$B$BNow, there''s just the matter of assulting Tiragarde Keep directly... It''s time to bring the humans some real pain.',0),
	 (90155,5,1,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Excellent work $N. This is the kind of attitude we need around here, if we''re to eliminate the infestation of the stinking human scum. We''re nearly done, and with this, a whole step closer to seeing tht dream come true.',0),
	 (90156,1,5,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Hopefullly the humans received our message loud and clear. Eliminating the last of their shelter, they have no where to turn, but home, or the grave. Their choice.$B$BI hope you''re ready to ensure exactly that happens.',0),
	 (90157,1,5,0,0,0,250,0,0,'Nothing like the taste of fresh human blood on your weapon after a clean kill. You are truly a service to your nation, $R. Now the human knights will have no chance to ride upon Razor Hill, endangering all that we''ve worked towards.$B$BHowever, there is still more to do.',0),
	 (90158,1,25,0,0,0,250,0,0,'<Gar''thok let''s out a deep rumble of laughter>$B$BThis is truly what it means to display your worthiness in a fight.$B$BThe cuts are a little rough, but I''m sure you''ll get better with practice. Here''s your reward for a well made trophy. ',0),
	 (90159,1,4,0,0,0,250,0,0,'While I wish I could have seen his ugly human face as you delivered your final blow, having his Insignia is nearly as good.$B$BWell done $C. You''ve made the Horde proud this day.$B$BLok''Tar!',0),
	 (90160,5,1,0,0,0,650,0,0,'Ah, there you are, $N. Your presence brings some much-needed assurance.
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90161,21,1,0,0,350,650,0,0,'You''ve shown great compassion, $N. The refugees you brought back are 
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90171,3,1,0,0,0,450,0,0,'Welcome back, $N. Your journey to the Deep Elm Mine was undoubtedly perilous, but the knowledge you''ve gained is invaluable. The presence of necromantic magic in such proximity to Ambermill is deeply concerning. It suggests a broader scheme at work, one that we must unravel if we are to protect these lands.$B$BWe will analyze your findings and determine our next course of action. Rest assured, $N, your efforts have brought us one step closer to understanding and combating this growing threat.',0),
	 (90172,1,66,0,0,250,450,0,0,'Each Ravenclaw felled by your hand is a step towards reclaiming the safety of our lands.$B$BThis victory, though significant, is but the first step in a much larger battle. Your actions have provided us with crucial time to prepare for what may come next. Thank you, $N. Your deeds today have proven you an invaluable defender of Ambermill. I fear your task is not yet quite complete, according to your report.',0),
	 (90173,1,21,0,0,0,450,0,0,'By burning the corpses of the Rotting Ravenclaw, you have severed the thread of necromancy that sought to reanimate them. This act is a testament to your determination and strength in facing such a dark challenge.$B$BThanks to your efforts, the Ravenclaw''s hold in the mine has been significantly weakened. You have not only protected Ambermill but have also struck a blow against the spread of this undead scourge. Your bravery is commendable, $N. We are in your debt.',0),
	 (90174,1,4,0,0,0,500,0,0,'Your return heralds a great victory, $N. The fall of Thule Ravenclaw is a significant blow to the darkness that creeps in Silverpine. By stopping his ritual, you have stemmed the flow of the undead and given us a chance to reclaim our lands.$B$BYour courage in the face of such overwhelming darkness is commendable. We are one step closer to cleansing these lands, thanks to your efforts. The path ahead remains fraught with danger, but today, we celebrate this triumph.',0),
	 (90175,1,2,0,0,0,500,0,0,'The news of Rogla''s defeat and the sealing of the Deathgate is a beacon of hope in these dark times, $N. Your ability to lead and rally others against such a fearsome adversary is a testament to your strength and resolve.$B$BThe victory you and your companions have achieved today is a major step in our fight against the undead scourge. Your bravery has not only saved countless lives but has also inspired those who fight alongside you. We are forever grateful for your heroism in the face of such daunting odds.',0),
	 (90176,1,1,0,0,0,350,0,0,'Your findings are deeply troubling, $N. The existence of the Wolf Cult confirms our worst fears. Their devotion to such a malevolent force could spell doom for us all if left unchecked.$B$BWe must remain vigilant and prepare to counter this new threat. Your efforts have provided us with crucial insight into our enemy. Thank you, $N. Your courage in the face of such darkness is a beacon of hope for us.',0),
	 (90177,1,21,0,0,0,400,0,0,'Your success in unmasking the spies is a crucial victory, $N. We can now interrogate them to learn more about Arugal''s plans. Your vigilance has safeguarded Pyrewood from immediate danger and disrupted the enemy''s flow of information.$B$BWe owe you a debt of gratitude. With your continued help, we might just turn the tide against these malevolent forces. Well done, $N.
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90181,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Your success in gathering the worg blood is a beacon of hope, $N. This may well be the first step in a long journey towards understanding and mitigating the curse''s effects on our people. The road ahead is fraught with uncertainty, but your efforts have illuminated a path through the darkness.',0),
	 (90182,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'The aroma of the chowder fills the air, a rare comfort in these dark times. Your efforts, $N, have brought a moment of peace to our people, a reminder that amidst the curse, there remains hope for tranquility. Thank you for this kindness, a beacon of light in the shadow of the Worgen Curse.',0),
	 (90183,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'These claws, $N, are more than mere trophies. They are symbols of your dominion over the beast within, a balance struck between your human intellect and the worgen''s raw power. Your success in this hunt speaks volumes of your strength and control. Well done.',0),
	 (90184,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'To stand before the full moon''s wrath and emerge unbroken is no small feat, $N. Your bravery this night has proven that even in our darkest hours, there lies within us a strength indomitable. The Bloodfang may have tested our resolve, but in you, they found their match. You have our thanks, and our respect.',0),
	 (90185,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Ah, $N, your prowess exceeds the tales. To eliminate a Son of Arugal to your own, that''s no small feat. It seems you''re full of surprises. Just remember, in this game of shadows and fangs, knowing when to bare your teeth and when to hide them is key. You''ve done well... for now.$B$BLet this victory serve not as a conclusion, but as a declaration of your newfound authority. Use it wisely, $N. The pack follows strength, and your actions have spoken volumes.',0),
	 (90187,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Seeing you sway hearts and minds, $N, it''s almost inspiring. Almost. Convincing the others to embrace their nature, to find balance within the curse, you''ve done more than simply recruit allies; you''ve kindled a flame of hope in these dark times.$B$BRemember, though, with great power comes... well, you know the rest. Keep a tight grip on that beast of yours, $N. We wouldn''t want it slipping its leash, now would we?',0),
	 (90188,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Your spirit burns brightly, $N. Few have the courage to face their inner turmoil, to seek harmony between light and shadow. You''ve shown not just bravery but a willingness to embrace your true nature.$B$BMy blessing is yours, child of the night. Walk the path with head held high, and let your howl echo through the ages. Remember, strength lies not in succumbing to the beast, but in mastering it. Go forth, with the fury of the wolf and the heart of a champion.',0),
	 (90189,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'The howls of victory echo through the village, a testament to your leadership and the ferocity of your pack. The Silverfangs underestimated the bond you''ve forged with your new allies. This victory is not just a testament to your strength but to the resolve and unity of the Moonrage Pack.$B$BYou''ve done more than just thwart an ambush, $N; you''ve sown the seeds of a legend. Pyrewood will sleep a bit easier tonight, thanks to you and your pack.',0),
	 (90190,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'The clash at Shadowfang Keep will be remembered as a turning point in our struggle against the Wolf Cult. Ivar Bloodfang''s retreat marks a significant victory for Pyrewood and the Moonrage Pack. You''ve led your pack with courage and tenacity, qualities that will serve us well in the battles to come.$B$B For now, we celebrate this triumph, $N. But let us not grow complacent. The war is far from over, and the shadow of Arugal still looms large. We must remain vigilant, prepared to defend our freedom at a moment''s notice.',0),
	 (90191,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Ah, $N, Lord Mayor Morrison speaks highly of you. Your deeds have echoed far beyond these cursed lands, it seems. The Alliance has not forgotten Gilneas, nor its people. We stand ready to aid those who share our values and our fight. Your presence here, now, is a testament to the resilience and valor of the Gilneans. Let''s see what can be done to bring your people into the fold, to stand united once more under the banner of the Alliance.',0);
INSERT INTO quest_offer_reward (ID,Emote1,Emote2,Emote3,Emote4,EmoteDelay1,EmoteDelay2,EmoteDelay3,EmoteDelay4,RewardText,VerifiedBuild) VALUES
	 (90192,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'Your journey here, and the story you bring, are compelling, $N. Gilneas has endured much, and its people have fought with the ferocity and courage befitting the Alliance. Your plea has not fallen on deaf ears.$B$BThe strength of the Alliance lies in unity, in the diverse peoples who stand together against the darkness. Let it be known that the Gilneans, with their indomitable spirit, shall take their place among us. Together, we will forge a future where no ally stands alone. Welcome, $N, and all of Gilneas, to the Alliance.',0),
	 (90194,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'The threat of that Dragonkin could never be ignored.
